# Dukkani Windsurf Rules

Follow these rules for all code generation, edits, and reviews in this repository.

## Source of truth

- Domain and package rules are maintained in `.cursor/rules/**/*.mdc`.
- Treat `.mdc` files as Markdown rule files and apply the rule matching the area you are editing.
- If a file-level rule conflicts with this file, prefer the more specific rule.

## Stack and workflow constraints

- Monorepo: Turborepo + pnpm workspaces.
- Apps live in `apps/*`; shared code lives in `packages/*`.
- Use internal imports via `@dukkani/*` package names.
- Use typed env values from `@dukkani/env`; avoid direct `process.env` in app code.
- Run commands from repository root unless a package script requires otherwise.

## Domain routing

- `apps/api/**` -> `.cursor/rules/apps/api.mdc`
- `apps/dashboard/**` -> `.cursor/rules/apps/dashboard.mdc`
- `apps/storefront/**` -> `.cursor/rules/apps/storefront.mdc`
- `apps/web/**` -> `.cursor/rules/apps/web.mdc`
- `packages/**` -> `.cursor/rules/packages/00-package-index.mdc` plus specific package rule

## Coding expectations

- Preserve package boundaries and avoid circular dependencies.
- Prefer shared package utilities instead of app-local duplication.
- Keep changes scoped to the requested task.
- Keep code and docs aligned with current monorepo architecture.

## Windsurf + Cursor parity

This project uses an include-based parity approach:

- Cursor reads `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` directly.
- Windsurf reads this `.windsurfrules` file, which points to the same canonical `.cursor/rules` content.
- Update `.cursor/rules` first, then keep this file aligned when domains change.
